      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and chill the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{plain-flour}}, {{icing-sugar}}, and {{sea-salt-fine}} in a bowl. Add the {{unsalted-butter}} cold butter and rub in until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Mix the {{egg-yolks}} egg yolk with the {{water}} cold water and add just enough to bring the dough together. Press into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blind bake the case",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C fan. Roll the chilled pastry to 3 mm thick and line a 23 cm loose-bottomed tart tin, pressing it into the fluted sides. Trim the overhang. Prick the base, line with baking paper, fill with baking beans, and bake for 15 minutes. Remove the beans and paper and bake for a further 8 minutes until the base is dry and just beginning to colour. Reduce the oven to 180°C fan.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the frangipane",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} softened butter and {{caster-sugar}} until pale and fluffy, about 4 minutes. Add the {{eggs}} eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add {{vanilla-extract}}. Fold in the {{almond-flour}} ground almonds and {{plain-flour}} sifted flour until combined. The frangipane should be smooth and hold its shape.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and bake, 35 to 40 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spread the frangipane evenly in the blind-baked case. Arrange the halved {{pear-conference}} Conference pears cut-side down on the frangipane, pressing them in gently. Scatter {{flaked-almonds}} flaked almonds over the top if using. Bake at 180°C fan for 35 to 40 minutes, until the frangipane is puffed, golden, and set firm when you gently shake the tin, no wobble. Cool in the tin for 20 minutes before releasing. If using the {{apricot-jam}} apricot glaze, brush it over the warm tart for a shine.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
